Tele - Comms wants out - of - market football . Tele - Communications Inc wants to be able to offer its cable television customers a package of National Football League out - of - market games , TCI executives said on Thursday . " We have to talk to them about giving our customers a fair shake , " Bob Thomson , TCI senior vice president and spokesman told a teleconference call held to explain the company ' s rate increases . Direct broadcast satellite ( DBS ) competitors are able to offer such packages . Thomson said in the past the NFL has cited resistance from local broadcasters as a reason for not offering the expanded games package to cable television companies . 
